The paper deals with food image recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of data augmentation techniques to improve the accuracy of the CNN model suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of different models and techniques for image classification indicates a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
